1
00:00:17,267 --> 00:00:18,184
<i>Max.</i>

2
00:00:20,770 --> 00:00:23,355
<i>Max. Max, can you hear me? Max.</i>

3
00:00:23,356 --> 00:00:26,526
<i>Come on. Open your eyes. Yes! Yes, Max!</i>

4
00:00:27,027 --> 00:00:28,110
Can you hear me?

5
00:00:28,111 --> 00:00:30,196
Max!

6
00:00:30,989 --> 00:00:32,615
Yes! Stay with me. Stay with me.

7
00:00:33,283 --> 00:00:34,242
All the way, Max.

8
00:00:36,077 --> 00:00:37,454
Yes! That's it! That's it!

9
00:00:43,168 --> 00:00:44,960
Hello, Lucas.

10
00:00:44,961 --> 00:00:50,175
Yes. Max. Come on, Max. It's me.
I'm right here. I'm right here, Max.

11
00:00:54,054 --> 00:00:58,767
Are you... Are you... Are you okay?
Do you... Do you hurt anywhere?

12
00:01:00,101 --> 00:01:04,189
I can't feel... much.

13
00:01:04,939 --> 00:01:07,859
Do you... Do you feel this?
Do you feel my hand?

14
00:01:08,902 --> 00:01:09,819
A little.

15
00:01:10,320 --> 00:01:12,530
Can... Can you... Can you see?

16
00:01:13,323 --> 00:01:18,578
The lights are really... are really bright.

17
00:01:19,621 --> 00:01:20,580
Hey.

18
00:01:21,081 --> 00:01:24,876
You haven't used your eyes, okay,
or your muscles for a long time.

19
00:01:25,919 --> 00:01:27,753
Okay, your body's just weak,

20
00:01:27,754 --> 00:01:30,840
but it just needs to readjust
and learn again.

21
00:01:32,509 --> 00:01:34,636
You are going to be okay.

22
00:01:35,261 --> 00:01:36,304
You're gonna be okay.

23
00:01:39,349 --> 00:01:41,017
I knew you were there.

24
00:01:42,477 --> 00:01:44,395
I always knew you were still there.

25
00:01:46,356 --> 00:01:47,941
I saw you.

26
00:01:49,109 --> 00:01:50,651
Waiting for me,

27
00:01:50,652 --> 00:01:54,239
playing my... my song.

28
00:01:55,865 --> 00:01:57,075
You bored of it yet?

29
00:02:00,703 --> 00:02:01,913
Are you?

30
00:02:07,418 --> 00:02:08,711
It turns out

31
00:02:10,296 --> 00:02:11,881
that the whole time,

32
00:02:14,050 --> 00:02:15,802
I didn't even need it.

33
00:02:17,720 --> 00:02:19,806
I just needed you.

34
00:02:22,642 --> 00:02:23,934
Just you.

35
00:02:23,935 --> 00:02:28,523
<i>I don't wanna swim forever</i>

36
00:02:30,066 --> 00:02:36,948
<i>When it's cold I'd like to die</i>

37
00:02:39,993 --> 00:02:43,162
<i>I don't wanna...</i>

38
00:02:43,163 --> 00:02:45,456
- Oh my God.
- Max.

39
00:02:47,959 --> 00:02:51,003
You're here. You're really here.

40
00:02:51,004 --> 00:02:52,589
I'm here.

41
00:02:53,381 --> 00:02:54,507
Hey, welcome home, kid.

42
00:02:56,801 --> 00:02:58,051
Took your sweet time, didn't you?

43
00:02:58,052 --> 00:03:00,388
Screw you, Wheeler.

44
00:03:06,269 --> 00:03:07,352
Where am I?

45
00:03:07,353 --> 00:03:08,687
Oh.

46
00:03:08,688 --> 00:03:11,565
Yeah, that would be confusing. Um...

47
00:03:11,566 --> 00:03:13,775
You were being hunted by the Demo-dogs,

48
00:03:13,776 --> 00:03:16,361
and we were all seconds away
from becoming lunch

49
00:03:16,362 --> 00:03:18,364
when Mrs. Wheeler came and...

50
00:03:19,616 --> 00:03:21,283
did the laundry.

51
00:03:21,284 --> 00:03:23,661
Holy shit! Mom!

52
00:03:25,246 --> 00:03:26,289
Vecna.

53
00:03:28,249 --> 00:03:29,542
He'll be angry.

54
00:03:30,585 --> 00:03:32,086
He'll try and find me.

55
00:03:33,463 --> 00:03:35,340
He'll know we escaped.

56
00:03:37,258 --> 00:03:38,218
Where's Holly?

57
00:03:41,012 --> 00:03:41,846
Where is she?

58
00:05:59,442 --> 00:06:00,777
Jonathan.

59
00:06:02,195 --> 00:06:04,530
Jonathan.

60
00:06:05,490 --> 00:06:06,783
Jonathan, stop.

61
00:06:08,493 --> 00:06:10,535
What?

62
00:06:10,536 --> 00:06:13,414
If we hurt ourselves,
we're really screwed.

63
00:06:14,665 --> 00:06:16,209
Yeah, I guess you're right.

64
00:06:19,128 --> 00:06:20,505
Oh, God.

65
00:06:23,174 --> 00:06:25,802
Okay, so now what?

66
00:06:26,386 --> 00:06:27,887
Anything else you wanna confess?

67
00:06:36,729 --> 00:06:37,939
Stay back.

68
00:06:47,031 --> 00:06:48,408
Sorry we're late.

69
00:06:53,246 --> 00:06:54,204
You okay?

70
00:06:54,205 --> 00:06:57,208
Yeah. Yeah, we're okay.

71
00:07:02,713 --> 00:07:03,923
Thanks.

72
00:07:05,675 --> 00:07:07,884
Was that weird? I'm sorry. That was weird.

73
00:07:07,885 --> 00:07:10,429
I didn't... We just... We both thought...

74
00:07:10,430 --> 00:07:12,681
- We were goners. Yeah, we did too.
- Yes.

75
00:07:12,682 --> 00:07:14,391
Turns out that shield generator of yours...

76
00:07:14,392 --> 00:07:16,768
Isn't really a shield generator.
Yeah, we know.

77
00:07:16,769 --> 00:07:20,021
Well, you'd think that would have been
good information to share.

78
00:07:20,022 --> 00:07:21,731
Well, we tried.

79
00:07:21,732 --> 00:07:22,899
Antenna snapped.

80
00:07:22,900 --> 00:07:24,151
His fault.

81
00:07:24,152 --> 00:07:26,903
Okay, so then what the hell did I shoot?

82
00:07:26,904 --> 00:07:28,447
Exotic matter.

83
00:07:28,448 --> 00:07:30,866
And we're supposed to know what that is?

84
00:07:30,867 --> 00:07:33,703
It's all in here. Look. Check this out.

85
00:07:34,871 --> 00:07:37,205
Dr. Brenner's notebook from '83.

86
00:07:37,206 --> 00:07:39,040
This thing is a gold mine.

87
00:07:39,041 --> 00:07:43,378
All his research into the gate,
how he created it, what it really is.

88
00:07:43,379 --> 00:07:45,213
I'm still deciphering it, but...

89
00:07:45,214 --> 00:07:47,174
Yeah, this shit will fry your brain.

90
00:07:47,175 --> 00:07:50,386
Cliff notes, Holly isn't
on the other side of the wall.

91
00:07:53,222 --> 00:07:54,640
Then where is she?

92
00:07:55,475 --> 00:07:57,601
I don't know... exactly.

93
00:07:57,602 --> 00:08:00,062
But wherever she is,
it's not the Upside Down.

94
00:08:21,626 --> 00:08:25,045
When he took me,
he opened the fourth, final gate,

95
00:08:25,046 --> 00:08:26,339
splitting Hawkins in two.

96
00:09:05,253 --> 00:09:06,629
You can do this.

97
00:09:33,823 --> 00:09:35,700
- What was that?
- What was what?

98
00:09:36,951 --> 00:09:38,286
Holly.

99
00:11:07,375 --> 00:11:09,084
Voyager Beta.

100
00:11:09,085 --> 00:11:10,086
Any signal yet?

101
00:11:11,420 --> 00:11:14,090
Negative, Voyager Alpha. Voyager Gamma?

102
00:11:14,674 --> 00:11:17,008
A big, fat zero over here.

103
00:11:17,009 --> 00:11:19,636
Your balloon experiment is a dud,
Snookums.

104
00:11:19,637 --> 00:11:22,555
Let's just put the antenna on the van
and drive.

105
00:11:22,556 --> 00:11:25,016
{\an8}As I've said, Voyager Gamma,
given the uneven terrain

106
00:11:25,017 --> 00:11:26,726
{\an8}and forested nature of Hawkins,

107
00:11:26,727 --> 00:11:29,104
a vehicle
is simply not the most expedient way

108
00:11:29,105 --> 00:11:30,563
to pinpoint a telemetry tag.

109
00:11:30,564 --> 00:11:33,358
{\an8}"Expedient"? We've been building
your goddamn balloon experiment

110
00:11:33,359 --> 00:11:34,275
{\an8}for six hours!

111
00:11:34,276 --> 00:11:37,028
{\an8}<i>Yes, but once we trilaterate
the three signals,</i>

112
00:11:37,029 --> 00:11:39,698
I'll be able to pinpoint
Dustin's precise location.

113
00:11:39,699 --> 00:11:42,492
You can't trilaterate shit
if we can't get a signal,

114
00:11:42,493 --> 00:11:45,495
so let's just cut our losses now

115
00:11:45,496 --> 00:11:48,582
before your star student winds up
dead in a ditch.

116
00:11:49,750 --> 00:11:51,252
"Cut our losses..."

117
00:11:59,218 --> 00:12:01,095
Fortune favors the bold.

118
00:12:04,432 --> 00:12:06,308
{\an8}I've secured a location on Dustin.

119
00:12:06,892 --> 00:12:08,268
Loose your balloons, Voyagers.

120
00:12:08,269 --> 00:12:10,019
- Come again?
- Wait, hold on. What?

121
00:12:10,020 --> 00:12:14,066
We need more height. Loose your balloons.

122
00:12:18,195 --> 00:12:19,572
Negative 80!

123
00:12:20,197 --> 00:12:21,865
Negative 44.

124
00:12:21,866 --> 00:12:25,160
I take it back, Snookums,
you mad, mad genius!

125
00:12:25,161 --> 00:12:28,164
Thank you, Voyager.
Calculations incoming. Hold tight.

126
00:12:41,969 --> 00:12:46,347
<i>You are going to be my spy</i>

127
00:12:46,348 --> 00:12:50,019
<i>one last time.</i>

128
00:12:55,483 --> 00:12:56,317
Will.

129
00:12:58,194 --> 00:13:00,111
Hopper just radioed.

130
00:13:00,112 --> 00:13:02,406
Max is safe. She got out.

131
00:13:04,325 --> 00:13:07,077
Hey, this is good news.

132
00:13:07,995 --> 00:13:10,872
None of this would have happened
if it weren't for you.

133
00:13:10,873 --> 00:13:12,124
Everything's gonna be okay.

134
00:13:12,792 --> 00:13:15,001
But for how long, Mom?

135
00:13:15,002 --> 00:13:17,879
If Lucas is right, today is the day,

136
00:13:17,880 --> 00:13:19,756
the day Vecna's gonna act.

137
00:13:19,757 --> 00:13:22,718
I thought I had him. But the truth...

138
00:13:23,969 --> 00:13:26,806
The truth is I never stood a chance.

139
00:13:28,015 --> 00:13:31,726
And he knew it. He's always known it.

140
00:13:31,727 --> 00:13:35,439
That's why, out of everyone in Hawkins,
he chose me.

141
00:13:36,482 --> 00:13:43,071
Because he knew I was weak,
and he knew he could control me.

142
00:13:43,072 --> 00:13:44,697
That is not true.

143
00:13:44,698 --> 00:13:46,950
It is, Mom. It is.

144
00:13:46,951 --> 00:13:48,744
I was his vessel.

145
00:13:49,745 --> 00:13:53,749
A vessel to channel his powers, to spy,

146
00:13:54,333 --> 00:13:56,585
<i>and... and to build.</i>

147
00:13:57,878 --> 00:14:00,213
"To... To build"?

148
00:14:00,214 --> 00:14:01,924
The tunnels.

149
00:14:02,967 --> 00:14:05,010
They didn't spread from the gate
on their own.

150
00:14:05,594 --> 00:14:10,932
<i>Every night, I jacked into the hive
and took control of the vines,</i>

151
00:14:10,933 --> 00:14:16,188
<i>using them to tunnel,
infecting our world with the Upside Down.</i>

152
00:14:17,064 --> 00:14:19,358
So many died because of me.

153
00:14:20,484 --> 00:14:22,695
<i>And if I could do all of that,</i>

154
00:14:23,529 --> 00:14:27,032
what could he do with 12 more like me?

155
00:14:27,616 --> 00:14:29,158
You listen to me.

156
00:14:29,159 --> 00:14:32,161
None of what happened is your fault.

157
00:14:32,162 --> 00:14:33,080
Do you hear me?

158
00:14:33,664 --> 00:14:35,999
And as for his big plan,

159
00:14:36,000 --> 00:14:39,085
he's not gonna have 12 vessels,
or whatever the hell he calls them,

160
00:14:39,086 --> 00:14:42,338
because he just lost Holly,
and she'll know where the others are.

161
00:14:42,339 --> 00:14:46,468
Sweetheart, this is not over,
not by a long shot.

162
00:14:47,636 --> 00:14:48,679
You're wrong.

163
00:14:49,471 --> 00:14:51,347
You're wrong, Mom.

164
00:14:51,348 --> 00:14:52,974
It's my fault.

165
00:14:52,975 --> 00:14:54,392
No.

166
00:14:54,393 --> 00:14:55,853
No, baby.

167
00:15:04,737 --> 00:15:06,280
Go! Go!

168
00:15:17,917 --> 00:15:20,168
<i>I couldn't see
where Holly was gonna wake up.</i>

169
00:15:20,169 --> 00:15:22,880
But I figured

170
00:15:23,923 --> 00:15:26,008
wherever Vecna was keeping her,

171
00:15:26,842 --> 00:15:28,802
it had to be in the Upside Down.

172
00:15:30,220 --> 00:15:31,221
So...

173
00:15:32,222 --> 00:15:35,600
I told her to just go home.

174
00:15:35,601 --> 00:15:37,644
Home? Home as in our home?

175
00:15:37,645 --> 00:15:40,313
Meaning we have to get
back into the Upside Down.

176
00:15:40,314 --> 00:15:42,941
- Where is the nearest rift to you?
- Off Cornwallis, I think.

177
00:15:42,942 --> 00:15:44,525
About a mile and a half, give or take.

178
00:15:44,526 --> 00:15:45,985
<i>Lucas, do you copy?</i>

179
00:15:45,986 --> 00:15:46,945
- Oh, Robin.
- Yeah.

180
00:15:46,946 --> 00:15:47,863
<i>Lucas!</i>

181
00:15:50,282 --> 00:15:52,158
Erica, I really can't talk right now.

182
00:15:52,159 --> 00:15:54,035
Okay, so Vecna took out those soldiers,

183
00:15:54,036 --> 00:15:56,079
so it should be a lot easier
to get into the MAC.

184
00:15:56,080 --> 00:15:57,914
No. They're gonna have reinforcements
by now.

185
00:15:57,915 --> 00:15:59,540
I can break through a plate.

186
00:15:59,541 --> 00:16:04,212
Are you saying that Holly is trapped
under a steel plate?

187
00:16:04,213 --> 00:16:06,422
Without context,
that might sound troubling,

188
00:16:06,423 --> 00:16:10,259
but she's not pancaked under a giant hunk
of steel or anything. She's...

189
00:16:10,260 --> 00:16:11,511
How do I talk about this?

190
00:16:11,512 --> 00:16:15,056
- Well, there's this world under ours...
- Under the plates.

191
00:16:15,057 --> 00:16:16,224
The Upside Down.

192
00:16:16,225 --> 00:16:18,893
Yeah, and it's just like Hawkins,
only way suckier.

193
00:16:18,894 --> 00:16:22,355
Guys, guys, guys.
Okay, you really won't believe this,

194
00:16:22,356 --> 00:16:26,026
but Erica and Mr. Clarke came through.
They found Dustin and the others.

195
00:16:27,194 --> 00:16:30,781
All right. Well, they're gonna be able
to find Holly a lot easier than we are.

196
00:16:33,409 --> 00:16:35,953
We better hurry. We got company.

197
00:16:47,923 --> 00:16:50,551
Hey, hey. Are you okay?

198
00:16:51,135 --> 00:16:52,427
I'm fine, Michael. I'm fine.

199
00:16:52,428 --> 00:16:54,887
No, with all due respect, Mrs. Wheeler,
you're not.

200
00:16:54,888 --> 00:16:58,516
You could get an infection, hemorrhage,
God forbid, stop breathing.

201
00:16:58,517 --> 00:17:02,854
If you think I'm gonna stay in bed
when my daughter needs me,

202
00:17:02,855 --> 00:17:06,024
you're out of your goddamn mind. Let's go.

203
00:17:06,025 --> 00:17:08,651
Mom, Mom, Mom, Mom. She's right.

204
00:17:08,652 --> 00:17:10,279
It's okay. Keep going.

205
00:17:10,863 --> 00:17:12,989
Hey, you saved us.

206
00:17:12,990 --> 00:17:14,532
You saved us.

207
00:17:14,533 --> 00:17:17,243
And by some miracle,
you're still here, okay?

208
00:17:17,244 --> 00:17:20,413
But now, you need to trust me that
we can handle this the rest of the way.

209
00:17:20,414 --> 00:17:23,541
There might be more of those things
out there.

210
00:17:23,542 --> 00:17:25,334
They're called Demogorgons. I know.

211
00:17:25,335 --> 00:17:29,797
There's so much that I need
to tell you about this Upside Down and El,

212
00:17:29,798 --> 00:17:31,632
but right now, all you need to know is

213
00:17:31,633 --> 00:17:34,886
that this group saved Will
when no one else could.

214
00:17:34,887 --> 00:17:36,179
We did that.

215
00:17:36,180 --> 00:17:38,389
And we're about to do the same thing
with Holly.

216
00:17:38,390 --> 00:17:42,436
We're gonna bring her back to you, Mom.
I promise. Okay?

217
00:17:43,937 --> 00:17:44,855
Yeah?

218
00:17:56,200 --> 00:17:58,493
Mr. Clarke, thanks for the assist.

219
00:17:58,494 --> 00:17:59,660
Don't thank me yet.

220
00:17:59,661 --> 00:18:02,288
We successfully trilaterated
Dustin's position here,

221
00:18:02,289 --> 00:18:03,748
to precisely where I stand now.

222
00:18:03,749 --> 00:18:06,042
But by the time we arrived, he was MIA.

223
00:18:06,043 --> 00:18:08,462
Well, he wouldn't be precisely here.
He'd be under.

224
00:18:09,463 --> 00:18:10,756
Sorry?

225
00:18:11,507 --> 00:18:12,758
You didn't tell him?

226
00:18:13,300 --> 00:18:14,759
- I...
- Told me what?

227
00:18:14,760 --> 00:18:16,512
Holy shit.

228
00:18:17,554 --> 00:18:18,847
Holy shit.

229
00:18:19,598 --> 00:18:21,433
Hey, over here! Over here!

230
00:18:23,143 --> 00:18:24,602
I got him! I got him!

231
00:18:24,603 --> 00:18:26,480
I got Dustin!

232
00:18:32,236 --> 00:18:33,946
- I don't hear anything.
- Patience.

233
00:18:35,322 --> 00:18:37,824
<i>Is anyone there? Repeat, this is Dustin.</i>

234
00:18:37,825 --> 00:18:40,243
Dustin, it's Mike.
Holly's escaped from Vecna,

235
00:18:40,244 --> 00:18:42,370
and she's on her way to my house
in the Upside Down.

236
00:18:42,371 --> 00:18:45,998
I need you to get there as fast as you can
and rendezvous with Holly. Do you copy?

237
00:18:45,999 --> 00:18:49,460
<i>Holly's not at the house.
We found her. We found Holly. Repeat, we--</i>

238
00:18:49,461 --> 00:18:50,963
Dustin, I'm losing you.

239
00:18:51,672 --> 00:18:52,589
Dustin?

240
00:18:54,800 --> 00:18:58,387
Am I going crazy, or did he just say
that he found Holly?

241
00:19:00,347 --> 00:19:03,057
All right, let's hug this wall up here.

242
00:19:03,058 --> 00:19:04,559
Why would she be at the lab?

243
00:19:04,560 --> 00:19:07,270
Wherever she escaped from,
the lab must've been en route to my house.

244
00:19:07,271 --> 00:19:09,730
She just happened to run into Dustin?
What are the odds?

245
00:19:09,731 --> 00:19:10,648
Low as shit,

246
00:19:10,649 --> 00:19:12,775
but I say it's about damn time
we had some luck.

247
00:19:12,776 --> 00:19:13,693
Amen to that.

248
00:19:13,694 --> 00:19:17,321
I'm sorry. I still don't follow.
Dustin is under those plates?

249
00:19:17,322 --> 00:19:18,657
- Yes.
- But not pancaked.

250
00:19:19,241 --> 00:19:20,617
Hang on. Hang on.

251
00:19:33,046 --> 00:19:35,465
Yeah, we got cameras all over that rift.

252
00:19:36,425 --> 00:19:38,759
I have an old spectrum analyzer
back at the club.

253
00:19:38,760 --> 00:19:41,929
If I can just locate their RF signal,
I should be able to jam the transmission.

254
00:19:41,930 --> 00:19:43,223
That's cool.

255
00:19:43,932 --> 00:19:45,559
I think you're overthinking it.

256
00:19:46,393 --> 00:19:49,103
You're telling me Alford
wouldn't have doubled that score?

257
00:19:49,104 --> 00:19:50,855
Four from six from the field.

258
00:19:50,856 --> 00:19:54,025
Reggie's gonna be something special,
you mark my words.

259
00:19:54,026 --> 00:19:55,360
Walsh can do no...

260
00:19:59,531 --> 00:20:01,116
You ain't seen nothing yet.

261
00:20:38,070 --> 00:20:39,946
You coming, Snookums?

262
00:20:39,947 --> 00:20:41,490
We're going in there?

263
00:20:42,658 --> 00:20:44,201
We're going in there.

264
00:20:46,203 --> 00:20:47,412
Steve!

265
00:20:47,913 --> 00:20:49,205
Dustin!

266
00:20:49,206 --> 00:20:50,539
Steve!

267
00:20:50,540 --> 00:20:52,124
Nancy! Holly!

268
00:20:52,125 --> 00:20:53,585
Jonathan!

269
00:20:59,883 --> 00:21:01,676
Is this shit safe to breathe?

270
00:21:01,677 --> 00:21:02,844
Unclear.

271
00:21:03,762 --> 00:21:04,721
Okay.

272
00:21:05,430 --> 00:21:07,807
Mike, any luck down there?

273
00:21:07,808 --> 00:21:10,185
Mike? Mike!

274
00:21:11,228 --> 00:21:12,437
Found him.

275
00:21:13,605 --> 00:21:15,274
Jesus, it's good to see you guys.

276
00:21:25,450 --> 00:21:26,410
Nancy?

277
00:21:28,120 --> 00:21:29,037
Where is she?

278
00:21:29,579 --> 00:21:30,872
Where's Holly?

279
00:21:36,503 --> 00:21:38,297
- What was that?
- What was what?

280
00:21:39,631 --> 00:21:40,924
Holly.

281
00:21:50,976 --> 00:21:53,769
Nancy! Nancy!

282
00:21:53,770 --> 00:21:55,563
- Holly! Holly!
- Nancy, help me!

283
00:21:55,564 --> 00:21:58,190
- Nancy, help me! Help me down, please!
- Holly!

284
00:21:58,191 --> 00:21:59,942
Nancy! Nancy, please!

285
00:21:59,943 --> 00:22:00,901
Holly!

286
00:22:00,902 --> 00:22:02,654
Nancy!

287
00:22:08,869 --> 00:22:13,832
<i>It was like something had a hold
of her, but you couldn't see anything.</i>

288
00:22:16,084 --> 00:22:17,252
It was him.

289
00:22:19,296 --> 00:22:21,173
Vecna. It had to be.

290
00:22:23,050 --> 00:22:23,883
<i>Mike?</i>

291
00:22:23,884 --> 00:22:26,927
Is Holly okay, Mike? Mike, do you copy?

292
00:22:26,928 --> 00:22:29,473
I repeat, is Holly okay?

293
00:23:16,895 --> 00:23:18,897
Don't worry, Holly.

294
00:23:19,856 --> 00:23:22,692
It will all be over soon.

295
00:23:24,611 --> 00:23:28,532
It will all be over.

296
00:23:33,412 --> 00:23:36,540
<i>It was some sort of demon,
a demon from that other world.</i>

297
00:23:37,207 --> 00:23:38,959
He can control monsters,

298
00:23:40,293 --> 00:23:41,585
move Humvees,

299
00:23:41,586 --> 00:23:43,130
stop fire.

300
00:23:45,757 --> 00:23:47,175
Bullets didn't touch him.

301
00:23:47,759 --> 00:23:49,260
Hell, nothing could.

302
00:23:49,261 --> 00:23:50,887
It wasn't a fight.

303
00:23:52,889 --> 00:23:54,641
It was a damn massacre.

304
00:23:59,813 --> 00:24:01,689
First we get mutant dogs at the hospital.

305
00:24:01,690 --> 00:24:03,274
Now a goddamn demon in the MAC?

306
00:24:03,275 --> 00:24:05,568
You wanna tell me what else
is about to pop out of that hellhole,

307
00:24:05,569 --> 00:24:07,027
or should we leave it a surprise?

308
00:24:07,028 --> 00:24:09,947
I don't know if you've noticed,
but suddenly we're light on men.

309
00:24:09,948 --> 00:24:11,699
Reinforcements are on the way.

310
00:24:11,700 --> 00:24:14,869
Any additional requests,
talk to your unit commander.

311
00:24:14,870 --> 00:24:17,580
How am I to know what to request
when I don't know what I'm fighting?

312
00:24:17,581 --> 00:24:21,625
You're not fighting anything.
This is not a war. It is a search.

313
00:24:21,626 --> 00:24:23,419
Something gets in your way, kill it.

314
00:24:23,420 --> 00:24:26,547
But otherwise,
keep your focus on finding the girl.

315
00:24:26,548 --> 00:24:29,133
Yeah, find the girl.
Christ, is that all you can say?

316
00:24:29,134 --> 00:24:32,179
I mean, you got a pull string
under that jacket of yours or what?

317
00:24:33,763 --> 00:24:36,474
Everything that has happened here
is because of that girl.

318
00:24:36,475 --> 00:24:39,185
And if you had just done your job
and found her,

319
00:24:39,186 --> 00:24:42,730
then I wouldn't have to repeat myself,
and we'd have those monsters in Moscow

320
00:24:42,731 --> 00:24:45,941
where they'd be killing Soviets
instead of Americans.

321
00:24:45,942 --> 00:24:48,235
The dead men, the children,

322
00:24:48,236 --> 00:24:50,906
their blood is on your hands, Lieutenant,
not mine.

323
00:24:51,490 --> 00:24:55,911
And unless you want to join them,
I would watch that goddamn tongue.

324
00:25:00,916 --> 00:25:03,585
<i>Lt. Akers, this is Bravo One. Do you copy?</i>

325
00:25:06,129 --> 00:25:07,254
Yeah, what is it?

326
00:25:07,255 --> 00:25:09,424
<i>We've got a rift breach at the old lab.</i>

327
00:25:10,217 --> 00:25:11,301
On my way.

328
00:25:19,226 --> 00:25:20,227
You okay?

329
00:25:20,936 --> 00:25:21,937
Max.

330
00:25:27,526 --> 00:25:32,988
So I leave you alone for a second,
and you turn into a sorcerer?

331
00:25:32,989 --> 00:25:37,076
It was a little more than a second,
and I'm not really a sorcerer.

332
00:25:37,077 --> 00:25:39,120
Mm, sure seemed like it to me.

333
00:25:40,622 --> 00:25:42,916
Hey, you up for a tour?

334
00:25:46,002 --> 00:25:48,254
Jimmy "Fast Hands" skipped town
before quarantine,

335
00:25:48,255 --> 00:25:50,130
so we just sort of moved in here.

336
00:25:50,131 --> 00:25:52,675
The basement is hidden
behind this bookshelf over there.

337
00:25:52,676 --> 00:25:54,593
Not quite the Batcave,
but it's pretty sweet.

338
00:25:54,594 --> 00:25:57,137
We kept the station going as cover.
Robin's our DJ.

339
00:25:57,138 --> 00:25:59,848
- Rockin' Robin.
- Rockin' Robin, my bad.

340
00:25:59,849 --> 00:26:01,392
And Steve's her sound man.

341
00:26:01,393 --> 00:26:02,394
Check this out.

342
00:26:15,699 --> 00:26:16,700
Hey...

343
00:26:17,534 --> 00:26:18,951
We're gonna get Holly back.

344
00:26:18,952 --> 00:26:21,454
She's all alone in there, Lucas.

345
00:26:22,038 --> 00:26:25,040
Alone with that monster.

346
00:26:25,041 --> 00:26:27,960
And I was so sure
that she could make it out.

347
00:26:27,961 --> 00:26:29,588
And I was so stupid.

348
00:26:30,088 --> 00:26:32,007
You had to try.

349
00:26:32,591 --> 00:26:34,134
I should have stayed there.

350
00:26:36,678 --> 00:26:38,305
And I should have kept her safe.

351
00:26:39,347 --> 00:26:40,974
Then we'd all be screwed.

352
00:26:41,474 --> 00:26:44,351
You've been in Vecna's mind.
You can help us beat him.

353
00:26:44,352 --> 00:26:46,855
No. I can't.

354
00:26:50,567 --> 00:26:52,818
I don't even know
where Vecna's keeping Holly.

355
00:26:52,819 --> 00:26:54,487
Well, it's a good thing I do.

356
00:26:56,031 --> 00:26:58,491
I know where she is,
but the real challenge is getting there.

357
00:26:59,701 --> 00:27:01,453
I gotta show you guys something.

358
00:27:02,996 --> 00:27:03,912
Okay.

359
00:27:03,913 --> 00:27:09,043
So, this is Hawkins,
and this is the Upside Down.

360
00:27:09,044 --> 00:27:12,463
We've always assumed the Upside Down
was another dimension opened by Brenner,

361
00:27:12,464 --> 00:27:15,592
but it turns out it's actually a bridge.

362
00:27:16,176 --> 00:27:18,302
More specifically,
an interdimensional bridge

363
00:27:18,303 --> 00:27:19,928
<i>that rips through space-time.</i>

364
00:27:19,929 --> 00:27:23,682
It is wildly unstable,
but held together by exotic matter,

365
00:27:23,683 --> 00:27:27,061
which we found dead center
right above the lab.

366
00:27:27,062 --> 00:27:28,437
<i>In theoretical physics,</i>

367
00:27:28,438 --> 00:27:30,856
- they call this type of bridge a...
- Wormhole.

368
00:27:30,857 --> 00:27:33,942
And this wormhole connects Hawkins
to here,

369
00:27:33,943 --> 00:27:37,529
another world that I've coined the Abyss.

370
00:27:37,530 --> 00:27:40,407
- Any particular reason?
- A realm of pure chaos and evil.

371
00:27:40,408 --> 00:27:42,284
- I'm sorry?
- D&D.

372
00:27:42,285 --> 00:27:43,869
- Jesus Christ.
- Wow.

373
00:27:43,870 --> 00:27:47,831
I believe this Abyss is the true home
of the Demogorgons,

374
00:27:47,832 --> 00:27:49,541
the vines, the Mind Flayer,

375
00:27:49,542 --> 00:27:51,960
all the nasty shit we found
in the Upside Down.

376
00:27:51,961 --> 00:27:54,046
It's where all those years ago
you banished Henry.

377
00:27:54,047 --> 00:27:55,255
<i>He was lost for years,</i>

378
00:27:55,256 --> 00:27:57,091
<i>and would've stayed lost
if it wasn't for Brenner.</i>

379
00:27:57,092 --> 00:27:59,009
He had me find Henry.

380
00:27:59,010 --> 00:28:02,554
And when you made remote contact
with the Abyss, the bridge formed.

381
00:28:02,555 --> 00:28:05,099
Ever since, Henry and his army
of monsters have been using it

382
00:28:05,100 --> 00:28:07,434
to cross right back into Hawkins.

383
00:28:07,435 --> 00:28:09,770
We kicked Vecna's ass last year,

384
00:28:09,771 --> 00:28:13,065
but he just fled across this bridge
back to the Abyss to lick his wounds.

385
00:28:13,066 --> 00:28:14,024
What a pussy.

386
00:28:14,025 --> 00:28:17,653
So all this time,
Vecna's been hiding in the sky?

387
00:28:17,654 --> 00:28:19,905
Explains why every crawl led
to a dead end.

388
00:28:19,906 --> 00:28:22,950
- And why I can't find him in the bath.
- And why Holly fell from the sky.

389
00:28:22,951 --> 00:28:24,952
Yeah, but why is he taking kids up there?

390
00:28:24,953 --> 00:28:26,537
For the same reason he took me.

391
00:28:26,538 --> 00:28:30,582
The minds of children are weaker, right?
More easily molded and controlled.

392
00:28:30,583 --> 00:28:34,253
So he channeled his thoughts and powers
through me to amplify his abilities,

393
00:28:34,254 --> 00:28:35,879
and he's gonna do the same
with those kids.

394
00:28:35,880 --> 00:28:37,632
Amplify his abilities?

395
00:28:38,174 --> 00:28:39,174
To do what?

396
00:28:39,175 --> 00:28:40,343
Move worlds.

397
00:28:42,512 --> 00:28:45,723
Holly, she said Henry told the kids

398
00:28:45,724 --> 00:28:49,561
that they would help him
draw the worlds together.

399
00:28:50,687 --> 00:28:53,021
I didn't understand
what that meant at the time, but...

400
00:28:53,022 --> 00:28:55,983
He wants to move the Abyss,
crash it into Hawkins.

401
00:28:55,984 --> 00:28:56,943
No, not crash.

402
00:28:57,527 --> 00:28:58,569
Merge.

403
00:28:58,570 --> 00:29:02,322
Henry wasn't licking his wounds
in the Abyss. He was making rifts,

404
00:29:02,323 --> 00:29:05,409
weakening the Abyss,
just like he weakened Hawkins.

405
00:29:05,410 --> 00:29:07,202
So when the Abyss and Hawkins collide...

406
00:29:07,203 --> 00:29:08,203
They become one.

407
00:29:08,204 --> 00:29:09,663
He's remaking the world.

408
00:29:09,664 --> 00:29:12,833
How long do we think this takes?
To move worlds?

409
00:29:12,834 --> 00:29:15,669
Are we talking like...
Or is this gonna take some time?

410
00:29:15,670 --> 00:29:18,297
We better hope we have some time.
Because if this is all correct,

411
00:29:18,298 --> 00:29:21,091
we have to get 2,000 feet in the air,
find our way into the Abyss,

412
00:29:21,092 --> 00:29:24,344
free Holly and the kids, and kill Vecna
all before our worlds merge.

413
00:29:24,345 --> 00:29:25,889
And if my theory's right,

414
00:29:26,598 --> 00:29:28,098
he's gonna move worlds tonight.

415
00:29:28,099 --> 00:29:30,017
Have I mentioned
how much I hate your theory?

416
00:29:30,018 --> 00:29:31,143
- Me too.
- Me three.

417
00:29:31,144 --> 00:29:33,812
I hate all of this.

418
00:29:33,813 --> 00:29:37,317
But at least now we know
what we're up against

419
00:29:37,942 --> 00:29:39,194
and what we need to do.

420
00:29:40,570 --> 00:29:42,030
We just need a plan.

421
00:30:03,718 --> 00:30:04,803
I'm sorry.

422
00:30:05,470 --> 00:30:07,638
I don't mean to pry. It's just...

423
00:30:07,639 --> 00:30:09,307
everyone's so worried.

424
00:30:10,391 --> 00:30:12,018
Is she gonna be okay?

425
00:30:18,024 --> 00:30:19,483
But you've told her, right,

426
00:30:19,484 --> 00:30:22,361
that this Max was just
a monster in disguise?

427
00:30:22,362 --> 00:30:25,072
That it was tricking her, lying.

428
00:30:25,073 --> 00:30:26,324
Of course.

429
00:30:27,033 --> 00:30:29,536
I've tried everything,
but she won't listen.

430
00:30:31,120 --> 00:30:33,705
We need her tonight, or we will fail.

431
00:30:33,706 --> 00:30:36,375
What did this Max tell her?

432
00:30:36,376 --> 00:30:39,754
Such awful, awful things.

433
00:30:40,255 --> 00:30:42,089
She told her I kidnapped you.

434
00:30:42,090 --> 00:30:43,841
- What?
- You rescued us.

435
00:30:43,842 --> 00:30:44,926
I know.

436
00:30:46,302 --> 00:30:48,012
That's not even the worst of it.

437
00:30:49,097 --> 00:30:52,975
She told her I don't wanna save the world.
I wanna end it.

438
00:30:52,976 --> 00:30:56,311
- How could she believe that?
- 'Cause she's stupid as shit, that's how.

439
00:30:56,312 --> 00:30:58,273
No, she's not stupid, Thomas.

440
00:30:59,315 --> 00:31:02,943
This monster is incredibly powerful,
and she works for the Black Thing.

441
00:31:02,944 --> 00:31:04,736
She has corrupted Holly's mind

442
00:31:04,737 --> 00:31:07,698
and dragged her out of the light
and taken her into the dark.

443
00:31:07,699 --> 00:31:11,159
Maybe we should just give up
and go home then.

444
00:31:11,160 --> 00:31:13,245
- Go home?
- To be with our parents.

445
00:31:13,246 --> 00:31:14,454
We would all die.

446
00:31:14,455 --> 00:31:15,622
What's wrong with you?

447
00:31:15,623 --> 00:31:16,957
Shut your trap, dipshit.

448
00:31:16,958 --> 00:31:19,167
Please let's not turn on each other.

449
00:31:19,168 --> 00:31:21,003
I know we're all upset.

450
00:31:21,004 --> 00:31:22,672
But perhaps Derek is right.

451
00:31:23,756 --> 00:31:27,468
Perhaps I have failed,
and the Black Thing has won.

452
00:31:28,344 --> 00:31:29,971
No, we can't let it win.

453
00:31:30,555 --> 00:31:32,390
Okay? We won't.

454
00:31:33,516 --> 00:31:35,309
You don't know Holly like we do.

455
00:31:35,310 --> 00:31:37,728
I've been her best friend
since kindergarten.

456
00:31:37,729 --> 00:31:39,146
Debbie's her second-best friend.

457
00:31:39,147 --> 00:31:41,440
- And she crushes hard on Josh.
- No, she doesn't.

458
00:31:41,441 --> 00:31:42,691
- She does.
- Totally.

459
00:31:42,692 --> 00:31:46,821
My point is, maybe if we all try
and talk to her, we can fix her.

460
00:31:47,488 --> 00:31:49,949
We can bring her back to the light.

461
00:31:50,617 --> 00:31:52,910
Mary's right. We can do it.

462
00:31:52,911 --> 00:32:07,674
Back to the light. Back to the light.
Back to the light. Back to the light.

463
00:32:07,675 --> 00:32:12,096
Back to the light.
Back to the light. Back to the light.

464
00:32:14,807 --> 00:32:18,102
As for the security cameras, trench plate...

465
00:32:18,603 --> 00:32:20,270
Not a bolt cutter.

466
00:32:20,271 --> 00:32:22,231
Yeah, you could safely say that, sir.

467
00:32:28,696 --> 00:32:30,281
She's getting reckless.

468
00:32:31,199 --> 00:32:32,367
Sloppy.

469
00:32:32,992 --> 00:32:34,451
Could be one of those damn monsters.

470
00:32:34,452 --> 00:32:37,079
A monster who breaks padlocks and cameras?

471
00:32:37,080 --> 00:32:38,665
I don't think so.

472
00:32:41,668 --> 00:32:42,669
It's her.

473
00:32:44,796 --> 00:32:47,255
Rally the rest of the team.
Tell them to lock and load.

474
00:32:47,256 --> 00:32:48,466
We're going in.

475
00:32:52,720 --> 00:32:57,642
At the base, in the Upside Down,
there's a chopper ready for the taking.

476
00:32:59,519 --> 00:33:03,731
We fly up to the Abyss,
kill the freak, rescue the kids,

477
00:33:04,691 --> 00:33:05,816
fly back down.

478
00:33:05,817 --> 00:33:07,651
Who do you expect to fly this thing?

479
00:33:07,652 --> 00:33:10,028
- It's a helicopter. They've got pilots.
- Right.

480
00:33:10,029 --> 00:33:12,280
- We force one to fly.
- Another kidnapping plot. Love it.

481
00:33:12,281 --> 00:33:14,533
How is this pilot gonna fly a chopper
into the rift?

482
00:33:14,534 --> 00:33:17,035
What do you mean? We just fly through it.

483
00:33:17,036 --> 00:33:18,161
- What?
- Idiot.

484
00:33:18,162 --> 00:33:19,413
Just fly through it?

485
00:33:19,414 --> 00:33:23,083
These rotors are like 40 feet wide.
It's too big. It's not gonna fit.

486
00:33:23,084 --> 00:33:25,502
Steve hears that all the time
and goes in anyway. Don't you?

487
00:33:25,503 --> 00:33:28,005
- What the hell is wrong with you?
- It's funny.

488
00:33:28,006 --> 00:33:29,131
Everybody shut up.

489
00:33:29,132 --> 00:33:33,552
Look, if somebody else has some magic bean
that I don't know about, I'm all ears.

490
00:33:33,553 --> 00:33:36,888
If not, it's a risk that we gotta take.
We fly, or we die.

491
00:33:36,889 --> 00:33:38,849
- Fly or die.
- Well, then I guess we die.

492
00:33:38,850 --> 00:33:41,768
We're not gonna die
if we commit to a plan.

493
00:33:41,769 --> 00:33:43,812
Can we weigh out
a few more options before...

494
00:33:43,813 --> 00:33:45,856
Yes. We die, I guess.

495
00:33:45,857 --> 00:33:48,984
- You said we have to get up 2,000 feet...
- Don't take that shit, Jim.

496
00:33:48,985 --> 00:33:50,861
- You're not listening to each other.
- You guys!

497
00:33:50,862 --> 00:33:52,071
How are you gonna do it?

498
00:33:53,072 --> 00:33:54,072
"Magic bean..."

499
00:33:54,073 --> 00:33:55,949
Can we get back on track?

500
00:33:55,950 --> 00:34:00,078
Let's not even try anything?

501
00:34:00,079 --> 00:34:01,830
We don't need a magic bean to climb.

502
00:34:01,831 --> 00:34:03,248
- ...an airplane!
- I'm not--

503
00:34:03,249 --> 00:34:04,709
We don't need a magic bean!

504
00:34:06,586 --> 00:34:10,173
Sorry. Just... We don't... We don't need it.

505
00:34:10,882 --> 00:34:12,090
A magic bean.

506
00:34:12,091 --> 00:34:14,469
We got a beanstalk right here.

507
00:34:22,351 --> 00:34:26,481
Okay, this flashlight is
the Squawk radio tower, and this Slinky...

508
00:34:27,899 --> 00:34:29,108
is the bridge.

509
00:34:29,609 --> 00:34:31,818
We'll never reach the Abyss
from the tower, right?

510
00:34:31,819 --> 00:34:35,030
But Max said Vecna is drawing
our worlds together.

511
00:34:35,031 --> 00:34:37,200
So, we let him.

512
00:34:37,825 --> 00:34:39,868
And we wait and wait

513
00:34:39,869 --> 00:34:43,538
as he draws it closer and closer.
When it's close enough,

514
00:34:43,539 --> 00:34:45,707
and the tower is poking
through one of the rifts,

515
00:34:45,708 --> 00:34:47,375
bam! El makes her move,

516
00:34:47,376 --> 00:34:50,045
she does her meditation thingy,
enters Vecna's sick mind

517
00:34:50,046 --> 00:34:51,004
and ambushes him.

518
00:34:51,005 --> 00:34:52,214
In your face, dickhead.

519
00:34:52,215 --> 00:34:55,051
And then, stopping the spell,
halting the worlds from moving.

520
00:34:56,010 --> 00:34:59,013
Wham, voilà!
We've got a beanstalk. It's perfect.

521
00:34:59,597 --> 00:35:02,015
All we gotta do
is climb up it into the Abyss.

522
00:35:02,016 --> 00:35:04,976
- I like it.
- It's not totally insane.

523
00:35:04,977 --> 00:35:07,062
- Thank you.
- But there's a problem, a big one.

524
00:35:07,063 --> 00:35:10,816
I can't reach inside Vecna's mind.
He's too far away.

525
00:35:10,817 --> 00:35:14,528
Can't you just try? I don't know, load up
on some of your junk food or something?

526
00:35:14,529 --> 00:35:16,197
Or better...

527
00:35:16,781 --> 00:35:17,824
We get you close.

528
00:35:18,449 --> 00:35:22,369
The Upside Down lab is under his lair,
and it's still frozen in time,

529
00:35:22,370 --> 00:35:25,330
which means everything should be there
from Brenner's experiments, including...

530
00:35:25,331 --> 00:35:26,665
The bath.

531
00:35:26,666 --> 00:35:30,293
If you do make it into his mind,
I can walk you through it,

532
00:35:30,294 --> 00:35:31,795
guide you.

533
00:35:31,796 --> 00:35:33,588
I know his sick mind inside and out.

534
00:35:33,589 --> 00:35:35,090
I should be there too.

535
00:35:35,091 --> 00:35:38,970
This plan hinges on stopping Henry,
and right now, Jane is fighting him alone.

536
00:35:40,179 --> 00:35:41,680
It doesn't need to be that way.

537
00:35:41,681 --> 00:35:44,142
I can follow her into his mind.

538
00:35:46,394 --> 00:35:48,937
We can end our brother, together.

539
00:35:48,938 --> 00:35:50,605
Okay, yeah, I dig it.

540
00:35:50,606 --> 00:35:53,651
Sisters kill their brother.
We rescue the kiddos, come home heroes.

541
00:35:54,235 --> 00:35:57,612
And if Lucas is right, we don't have
a lot of time, so we have to move fast.

542
00:35:57,613 --> 00:35:58,697
One final thing.

543
00:35:58,698 --> 00:35:59,865
Cherry on top.

544
00:35:59,866 --> 00:36:04,871
On the way out,
we drop a bomb near the exotic matter.

545
00:36:05,913 --> 00:36:08,791
Set a timer, escape the Upside Down.

546
00:36:10,710 --> 00:36:12,753
The bridge collapses, and with it,

547
00:36:13,379 --> 00:36:18,301
the Abyss, the Demos,
the Mind Flayer, all of it, gone.

548
00:36:18,801 --> 00:36:20,970
Game. Set. Match.

549
00:36:27,935 --> 00:36:29,311
Holly! Holly!

550
00:36:29,312 --> 00:36:32,690
Hey. It's okay. You're safe.

551
00:36:33,191 --> 00:36:35,651
You're safe now. You're with us. Okay?

552
00:36:38,696 --> 00:36:40,197
Welcome back, Holly.

553
00:36:40,198 --> 00:36:41,699
Welcome.

554
00:36:42,700 --> 00:36:44,117
Where is he?

555
00:36:44,118 --> 00:36:45,536
Mr. Whatsit?

556
00:36:46,454 --> 00:36:47,287
Downstairs.

557
00:36:47,288 --> 00:36:48,496
He's worried about you.

558
00:36:48,497 --> 00:36:49,623
So worried.

559
00:36:49,624 --> 00:36:52,584
No, no, no, no, no.
Mary, you need to listen.

560
00:36:52,585 --> 00:36:55,795
Mr. Whatsit, he's not who he says he is.
He didn't really save us.

561
00:36:55,796 --> 00:36:57,298
- He--
- He's kidnapped us?

562
00:36:57,798 --> 00:37:01,092
He's trying to destroy the world?
Holly, Mr. Whatsit has told us everything.

563
00:37:01,093 --> 00:37:04,054
Those are lies. Evil, nasty lies!

564
00:37:04,055 --> 00:37:07,058
- No, they're not! They're not--
- That other girl you met, Max.

565
00:37:07,558 --> 00:37:08,600
She's not a human.

566
00:37:08,601 --> 00:37:09,643
She's a monster.

567
00:37:09,644 --> 00:37:10,852
She twisted your mind.

568
00:37:10,853 --> 00:37:12,647
That's not true.

569
00:37:13,356 --> 00:37:14,481
Max is a friend,

570
00:37:14,482 --> 00:37:16,024
and she's... she's helping us.

571
00:37:16,025 --> 00:37:19,695
She's helping us get back home,
back to our families.

572
00:37:20,279 --> 00:37:21,404
We're all trapped.

573
00:37:21,405 --> 00:37:23,531
Trapped in Mr. Whatsit's mind.

574
00:37:23,532 --> 00:37:26,285
Everything you see, none of it is real!

575
00:37:26,786 --> 00:37:28,329
Come on, you have to believe me.

576
00:37:29,038 --> 00:37:29,914
Please.

577
00:37:30,498 --> 00:37:34,960
You have to believe me.
You have to believe me.

578
00:37:34,961 --> 00:37:36,128
You gotta believe me.

579
00:37:38,839 --> 00:37:40,132
Derek.

580
00:37:41,968 --> 00:37:43,094
Derek, tell them.

581
00:37:44,845 --> 00:37:46,722
Tell them. Tell them!

582
00:37:54,480 --> 00:37:55,981
They're right, Holly.

583
00:37:55,982 --> 00:37:57,608
Max lied to us.

584
00:38:06,534 --> 00:38:09,370
I don't... understand.

585
00:38:10,246 --> 00:38:12,123
Everything she showed me just...

586
00:38:13,791 --> 00:38:16,002
seemed so real.

587
00:38:18,587 --> 00:38:20,672
I knew not to go into the woods.

588
00:38:20,673 --> 00:38:24,593
But I... I went there anyway, and...

589
00:38:25,636 --> 00:38:27,638
And I just... I just feel so...

590
00:38:31,100 --> 00:38:32,268
so stupid.

591
00:38:32,768 --> 00:38:35,854
- You're not stupid, Holly.
- None of this is your fault.

592
00:38:35,855 --> 00:38:36,897
Holly.

593
00:38:37,898 --> 00:38:41,944
You know, the important thing is that
you're here. You're here just in ti--

594
00:38:42,737 --> 00:38:44,238
Holly, stop it!

595
00:38:49,118 --> 00:38:50,786
Bitch! Get her!

596
00:38:52,913 --> 00:38:54,165
Get her!

597
00:39:44,090 --> 00:39:49,512
Well, I was hoping
for a slightly more delicate landing, but...

598
00:39:50,179 --> 00:39:51,972
I suppose that'll do.

599
00:39:54,266 --> 00:39:55,434
You're welcome.

600
00:39:59,105 --> 00:40:01,689
{\an8}Of all the people she had
to go with, it had to be her.

601
00:40:01,690 --> 00:40:04,734
El trusts her. Maybe we should too.

602
00:40:04,735 --> 00:40:08,239
No, she's up to something.
I'm sure of it. I just...

603
00:40:09,240 --> 00:40:11,116
El's not gonna listen to me.

604
00:40:11,117 --> 00:40:13,577
What happened to the two of you
down there?

605
00:40:15,579 --> 00:40:17,206
She thinks I don't believe in her.

606
00:40:18,249 --> 00:40:20,583
- Which isn't true.
- No, of course not.

607
00:40:20,584 --> 00:40:22,336
Well, have you told her that?

608
00:40:23,087 --> 00:40:24,838
She thinks she's invincible,

609
00:40:24,839 --> 00:40:26,882
and that's not the case.

610
00:40:27,466 --> 00:40:29,467
Yeah, that's not what I asked.

611
00:40:29,468 --> 00:40:32,804
I can work on repairing things between us
when I get on the other side of this,

612
00:40:32,805 --> 00:40:36,307
but right now, I need to make sure
she gets out of this alive.

613
00:40:36,308 --> 00:40:40,312
That Kali makes one false move,
I swear to God, I'm gonna kill her.

614
00:40:40,813 --> 00:40:42,605
I'm gonna kill her. I will not hesitate.

615
00:40:42,606 --> 00:40:45,192
Anything happens to El in that tank,
I am pulling her out.

616
00:40:46,652 --> 00:40:48,195
I can't lose her, Joyce.

617
00:40:51,490 --> 00:40:52,783
I can't.

618
00:40:58,330 --> 00:40:59,957
One last crawl.

619
00:41:01,917 --> 00:41:03,294
One last crawl.

620
00:41:17,391 --> 00:41:20,019
It gives me a headache
trying to understand all this.

621
00:41:21,479 --> 00:41:26,734
But I think I got a C- in physics,
so I'll trust the nerds.

622
00:41:28,110 --> 00:41:30,987
Do you think it'll work? The plan?

623
00:41:30,988 --> 00:41:33,324
I mean, it has to, right?

624
00:41:34,825 --> 00:41:36,827
I just wish I wasn't stuck here.

625
00:41:37,453 --> 00:41:38,745
I feel useless.

626
00:41:38,746 --> 00:41:42,081
El and Kali are gonna need you
in the mind. I'm the one who's useless.

627
00:41:42,082 --> 00:41:44,292
You can still go there, to the Abyss.

628
00:41:44,293 --> 00:41:46,085
It's too risky.

629
00:41:46,086 --> 00:41:49,506
I'd be at the heart of the hive mind,
and I don't know what would happen.

630
00:41:49,507 --> 00:41:53,218
Last time I got too close, he used me
to spy, and it almost got you killed, Max.

631
00:41:53,219 --> 00:41:55,512
You also saved my life, remember?

632
00:41:55,513 --> 00:41:59,349
Plus, I've been almost killed plenty
of times at the hands of this asshole,

633
00:41:59,350 --> 00:42:01,476
so I'm kind of used to it at this point.

634
00:42:01,477 --> 00:42:05,939
How did you survive in there,
this whole time in Henry's mind?

635
00:42:05,940 --> 00:42:07,608
Honestly, luck.

636
00:42:09,151 --> 00:42:10,694
I found this cave.

637
00:42:11,195 --> 00:42:13,613
It was this old memory of his,

638
00:42:13,614 --> 00:42:16,158
and he was terrified of it.

639
00:42:17,284 --> 00:42:18,285
He wouldn't go in.

640
00:42:19,078 --> 00:42:20,912
Scared the living shit out of him.

641
00:42:20,913 --> 00:42:23,831
Underneath all those scars,
he's still human.

642
00:42:23,832 --> 00:42:28,754
A psychopath
with a serious god complex, but...

643
00:42:29,964 --> 00:42:31,297
human.

644
00:42:31,298 --> 00:42:35,219
I guess
we're all scared of something, right?

645
00:42:45,604 --> 00:42:47,814
Okay, Wheeler, how's it going
with your contraption?

646
00:42:47,815 --> 00:42:52,902
{\an8}Okay, so just imagine that this bike bell
is the bomb's remote trigger, okay?

647
00:42:52,903 --> 00:42:56,155
{\an8}So when this wire touches
this warrior here, kaboom.

648
00:42:56,156 --> 00:42:57,324
{\an8}Genius.

649
00:42:57,825 --> 00:43:00,827
{\an8}One thing is, I don't know
if we can blow up the Upside Down

650
00:43:00,828 --> 00:43:02,829
{\an8}to the dulcet tones
of the Butthole Surfers.

651
00:43:02,830 --> 00:43:04,998
I built the bomb.
I should be able to pick the record.

652
00:43:04,999 --> 00:43:06,291
You <i>can</i> pick the record.

653
00:43:06,292 --> 00:43:09,002
You just have to follow one simple rule,
which is pick a good record.

654
00:43:09,003 --> 00:43:10,044
This is a great record!

655
00:43:10,045 --> 00:43:13,089
As far as save-the-world soundtracks goes,
this one's lacking.

656
00:43:13,090 --> 00:43:14,215
What would you pick?

657
00:43:14,216 --> 00:43:16,676
The Replacements.
I can't not think of better records.

658
00:43:16,677 --> 00:43:18,887
Okay, enough, Lester Bangs, okay?

659
00:43:20,723 --> 00:43:22,307
Hey. Hey!

660
00:43:22,308 --> 00:43:24,183
Have you handled one of these before?

661
00:43:24,184 --> 00:43:30,399
Not exactly, but, you know, BB guns,
air rifles... ...<i>Duck Hunt.</i>

662
00:43:30,983 --> 00:43:32,025
<i>Duck Hunt.</i>

663
00:43:32,026 --> 00:43:33,402
He is remarkably good at it.

664
00:43:35,821 --> 00:43:37,156
But I have a better idea.

665
00:43:37,823 --> 00:43:38,824
Come on.

666
00:43:48,167 --> 00:43:50,294
These babies are deadlier than they look.

667
00:43:53,255 --> 00:43:54,589
You sure?

668
00:43:54,590 --> 00:43:55,841
Mm.

669
00:43:59,219 --> 00:44:00,178
- Hey, Dustin?
- Yeah?

670
00:44:00,179 --> 00:44:03,514
Hey, about, uh, some of the stuff
that I said earlier. I just--

671
00:44:03,515 --> 00:44:05,893
- It's fine. It's okay.
- No, just...

672
00:44:06,727 --> 00:44:08,103
It's not okay.

673
00:44:11,023 --> 00:44:12,024
Eddie...

674
00:44:13,776 --> 00:44:15,152
He saved your life.

675
00:44:16,904 --> 00:44:18,155
Our lives.

676
00:44:19,156 --> 00:44:22,910
And I know what he meant to you.
I can't even imagine how hard it's been.

677
00:44:23,452 --> 00:44:24,787
But instead of...

678
00:44:26,664 --> 00:44:28,707
just being there for you, I just...

679
00:44:31,168 --> 00:44:34,046
Well, I got angry about it. I guess...

680
00:44:36,674 --> 00:44:38,300
I got angry because

681
00:44:40,094 --> 00:44:41,470
things were different.

682
00:44:44,139 --> 00:44:45,057
Because...

683
00:44:47,142 --> 00:44:48,477
I really missed you.

684
00:44:52,773 --> 00:44:54,316
I missed my best friend.

685
00:44:57,861 --> 00:44:59,738
Yeah, I missed my best friend too.

686
00:45:13,210 --> 00:45:16,463
For the record, a Rubik's Cube
isn't even a good measure of intelligence.

687
00:45:18,590 --> 00:45:21,634
And your beanstalk plan, seriously,
only a genius could've come up with that.

688
00:45:21,635 --> 00:45:22,761
Yeah, well...

689
00:45:23,804 --> 00:45:25,054
I learned from the best.

690
00:45:25,055 --> 00:45:26,556
That's true.

691
00:45:26,557 --> 00:45:28,474
Silver lining.

692
00:45:28,475 --> 00:45:30,519
If it fails, we both go down.

693
00:45:31,437 --> 00:45:33,147
You die, I die.

694
00:45:36,900 --> 00:45:37,901
You die, I die.

695
00:45:56,044 --> 00:46:02,718
Gate opening in five, four, three, two...

696
00:46:05,596 --> 00:46:06,847
Open sesame.

697
00:46:08,932 --> 00:46:09,850
Gotcha!

698
00:46:11,226 --> 00:46:14,896
We've secured the gate signal.
Repeat. Gate signal is secure.

699
00:46:14,897 --> 00:46:17,899
Tell Snookums his timing is mwah!

700
00:46:17,900 --> 00:46:20,027
Because Santa's sleigh...

701
00:46:22,279 --> 00:46:23,947
...is almost ready.

702
00:46:25,574 --> 00:46:27,284
Piece of shit!

703
00:46:28,744 --> 00:46:31,079
Oh God! Oh God!

704
00:46:31,622 --> 00:46:34,373
Why?! Why?!
Why do you gotta do this right now?

705
00:46:34,374 --> 00:46:36,000
What? You don't like me? Huh?

706
00:46:36,001 --> 00:46:38,211
It's not me! I'm not the one!
I'm not the one who...

707
00:46:38,212 --> 00:46:39,463
Hi, sister.

708
00:46:40,631 --> 00:46:41,714
Hi.

709
00:46:41,715 --> 00:46:44,050
Have you ever done this before?

710
00:46:44,051 --> 00:46:45,719
Shared your mind like this?

711
00:46:48,180 --> 00:46:49,097
Have you?

712
00:46:50,098 --> 00:46:52,017
With my other psychic friends
all the time.

713
00:46:53,644 --> 00:46:54,978
I'm glad I'm here.

714
00:46:55,479 --> 00:46:56,354
Me too.

715
00:46:56,355 --> 00:46:58,023
Even after yesterday?

716
00:47:00,400 --> 00:47:01,777
Have you thought about it?

717
00:47:02,277 --> 00:47:03,695
What it all means?

718
00:47:04,905 --> 00:47:10,619
I was thinking when we blow up the bridge,
we'll blow up Dr. Kay's lab.

719
00:47:11,495 --> 00:47:12,954
We'll end her experiment.

720
00:47:12,955 --> 00:47:14,455
Kay will simply make a new lab.

721
00:47:14,456 --> 00:47:15,623
So we kill her.

722
00:47:15,624 --> 00:47:18,501
She replaced Papa.
Another will replace her.

723
00:47:18,502 --> 00:47:20,711
We can go away somewhere.
We can hide from them.

724
00:47:20,712 --> 00:47:23,090
Oh, like somewhere
with at least one waterfall?

725
00:47:24,758 --> 00:47:26,592
It's a fantasy, Jane.

726
00:47:26,593 --> 00:47:29,428
If you flee with Mike,
maybe you're safe for a while.

727
00:47:29,429 --> 00:47:31,597
But when they find you, and they will,

728
00:47:31,598 --> 00:47:35,309
they will kill Mike,
just as they killed my friends.

729
00:47:35,310 --> 00:47:37,645
Then they will take you,
and with your blood,

730
00:47:37,646 --> 00:47:40,982
they will create more children,
children who will suffer as we have.

731
00:47:40,983 --> 00:47:45,695
And with these children,
they will open up more gates, more worlds.

732
00:47:45,696 --> 00:47:46,989
Don't you see, Jane?

733
00:47:47,865 --> 00:47:49,157
It's a cycle.

734
00:47:49,741 --> 00:47:52,995
A terrible, vicious cycle.

735
00:47:53,996 --> 00:47:55,372
But we can stop it.

736
00:47:57,040 --> 00:47:58,041
Tonight.

737
00:48:06,550 --> 00:48:07,801
How?

738
00:48:08,385 --> 00:48:10,261
After we kill our brother,

739
00:48:10,262 --> 00:48:12,179
after the children are rescued,

740
00:48:12,180 --> 00:48:14,224
we don't leave with the others.

741
00:48:14,725 --> 00:48:15,850
We stay on the bridge.

742
00:48:15,851 --> 00:48:18,228
When the Upside Down vanishes...

743
00:48:21,523 --> 00:48:22,858
so will we.

744
00:48:24,902 --> 00:48:26,945
It is the only way, Jane.

745
00:48:27,613 --> 00:48:29,656
The only way.

746
00:48:33,827 --> 00:48:36,037
You ladies done meditating?

747
00:48:36,038 --> 00:48:39,207
'Cause Santa's sleigh is ready to fly!

748
00:49:05,901 --> 00:49:06,944
Mom?

749
00:49:08,820 --> 00:49:09,905
Um...

750
00:49:12,074 --> 00:49:17,119
Earlier today when you asked me
what happened in Vecna's mind,

751
00:49:17,120 --> 00:49:19,456
I didn't tell you everything.

752
00:49:22,668 --> 00:49:24,710
When Vecna attacks,

753
00:49:24,711 --> 00:49:29,674
he weakens you
by turning your own mind against you,

754
00:49:29,675 --> 00:49:33,512
by bringing out everything inside you
that hurts.

755
00:49:34,304 --> 00:49:39,600
So I fought back
by focusing on happy memories,

756
00:49:39,601 --> 00:49:42,687
memories from when I was a kid,

757
00:49:42,688 --> 00:49:44,564
and when I wasn't scared,

758
00:49:45,482 --> 00:49:47,234
and when I felt most happy.

759
00:49:48,402 --> 00:49:50,945
<i>That's how I took control in the MAC-Z</i>

760
00:49:50,946 --> 00:49:53,031
and how I killed those Demos.

761
00:49:53,615 --> 00:49:55,700
And I thought the same would work
on Vecna too.

762
00:49:55,701 --> 00:49:57,452
But he found a way past.

763
00:50:00,247 --> 00:50:01,957
And he showed me things, Mom.

764
00:50:04,793 --> 00:50:07,545
He showed me the most awful things.

765
00:50:07,546 --> 00:50:09,005
No, listen.

766
00:50:09,006 --> 00:50:13,259
Whatever he showed you, it's not real.
He plays tricks. He lies.

767
00:50:13,260 --> 00:50:15,429
No, he doesn't.

768
00:50:16,680 --> 00:50:18,140
What he showed me...

769
00:50:20,017 --> 00:50:21,768
it didn't come from him.

770
00:50:23,186 --> 00:50:24,521
It came from me.

771
00:50:26,314 --> 00:50:28,483
He sees everything, Mom.

772
00:50:29,109 --> 00:50:31,778
He sees my thoughts.

773
00:50:32,487 --> 00:50:34,239
He sees my memories.

774
00:50:34,990 --> 00:50:39,703
And he sees my secrets.

775
00:50:40,579 --> 00:50:45,792
But Max, she told me he's also afraid,
which proves I can beat him.

776
00:50:46,501 --> 00:50:49,254
But for me to do that,

777
00:50:50,756 --> 00:50:51,965
you need to know...

778
00:50:56,720 --> 00:50:59,097
I think you need to know the truth.

779
00:51:02,350 --> 00:51:03,684
Oh. Uh...

780
00:51:03,685 --> 00:51:05,770
Sorry. We just heard from Hop.

781
00:51:05,771 --> 00:51:08,607
He's 15 minutes out.
So we should probably leave in five.

782
00:51:09,691 --> 00:51:11,067
Is everything okay?

783
00:51:11,068 --> 00:51:12,652
Yeah, we'll be out in a minute.

784
00:51:14,613 --> 00:51:15,614
Wait.

785
00:51:17,032 --> 00:51:18,784
I think you need to hear this too.

786
00:51:20,035 --> 00:51:21,328
Everyone does.

787
00:51:29,503 --> 00:51:30,420
I...

788
00:51:31,588 --> 00:51:35,926
I... I haven't told any of you this

789
00:51:36,718 --> 00:51:37,719
because...

790
00:51:39,387 --> 00:51:44,683
Because I... I don't... I don't want you
to see me differently.

791
00:51:44,684 --> 00:51:46,561
But the truth is...

792
00:51:47,521 --> 00:51:51,315
The... The truth is I am.

793
00:51:51,316 --> 00:51:52,609
I am different.

794
00:51:53,819 --> 00:51:54,694
I just...

795
00:51:55,445 --> 00:51:59,241
I just pretended like I wasn't
because... because I didn't want to be.

796
00:51:59,825 --> 00:52:04,287
I wanted to be like everyone else.
I wanted to be like my friends and...

797
00:52:05,372 --> 00:52:06,665
And I am like you.

798
00:52:07,207 --> 00:52:10,000
I'm like you in... in almost every way.

799
00:52:10,001 --> 00:52:12,336
We... We like playing
D&D late into the night.

800
00:52:12,337 --> 00:52:14,880
And we like that old-person smell
in Mike's basement.

801
00:52:14,881 --> 00:52:19,176
And we... we like biking to Melvald's
for malted milkshakes.

802
00:52:19,177 --> 00:52:22,012
And we like getting lost in the woods,

803
00:52:22,013 --> 00:52:25,057
and getting lost in Family Video
and arguing about what to rent

804
00:52:25,058 --> 00:52:27,852
and settling on <i>Holy Grail</i>
for the millionth time.

805
00:52:27,853 --> 00:52:31,522
And... And we like Milk Duds
in our popcorn with extra butter.

806
00:52:31,523 --> 00:52:34,859
And we like drinking Coke with Pop Rocks.

807
00:52:34,860 --> 00:52:37,820
And we like bike races and trading comics

808
00:52:37,821 --> 00:52:41,699
and NASA and Steve Martin
and Lucky Charms and...

809
00:52:41,700 --> 00:52:43,284
Literally all the same things.

810
00:52:43,285 --> 00:52:47,580
I just... I just... I... I just...

811
00:52:47,581 --> 00:52:48,707
I...

812
00:52:50,667 --> 00:52:51,710
I...

813
00:52:52,419 --> 00:52:53,460
I...

814
00:52:53,461 --> 00:52:55,380
I don't like girls.

815
00:53:08,602 --> 00:53:09,603
I mean...

816
00:53:10,478 --> 00:53:15,066
I mean I do. Just...
Just not like you guys do.

817
00:53:15,650 --> 00:53:19,737
And I, uh, I had this...
this crush on someone,

818
00:53:19,738 --> 00:53:22,908
even though I know...
I know they're not like me.

819
00:53:24,659 --> 00:53:27,536
But... But then I realized
he's just my Tammy.

820
00:53:27,537 --> 00:53:30,456
And by Tammy,
I mean it was never about him.

821
00:53:30,457 --> 00:53:32,082
It was... It was about me.

822
00:53:32,083 --> 00:53:35,211
And I thought
I was finally okay with myself,

823
00:53:35,212 --> 00:53:37,588
but... but then today...

824
00:53:37,589 --> 00:53:40,799
Today Vecna showed me what would happen
if I did this,

825
00:53:40,800 --> 00:53:43,762
if I told you guys the truth.

826
00:53:44,346 --> 00:53:47,473
He showed me a future, and in this future,

827
00:53:47,474 --> 00:53:51,060
some of you are just...
are just worried for me.

828
00:53:51,061 --> 00:53:53,270
Worried that things will be harder for me.

829
00:53:53,271 --> 00:53:56,565
And it just makes me feel like
something's wrong with me.

830
00:53:56,566 --> 00:53:58,192
So I... So I push you away.

831
00:53:58,193 --> 00:54:01,487
And for the rest of us,
we just drift apart more

832
00:54:01,488 --> 00:54:05,282
and more and more
and more and more until I'm alone.

833
00:54:05,283 --> 00:54:08,953
And I know none of that has happened,
and Vecna can't see into the future.

834
00:54:08,954 --> 00:54:11,830
But he can see into our minds,
and he knows things.

835
00:54:11,831 --> 00:54:16,502
And it just felt so real. It felt so real.

836
00:54:16,503 --> 00:54:17,711
Will.

837
00:54:17,712 --> 00:54:19,630
You gotta listen to me.

838
00:54:19,631 --> 00:54:22,091
That will never ever happen.

839
00:54:22,092 --> 00:54:24,219
You'll never lose me.

840
00:54:24,970 --> 00:54:25,844
Ever.

841
00:54:25,845 --> 00:54:28,598
Okay. Okay.

842
00:54:29,266 --> 00:54:30,850
And you'll never lose me.

843
00:54:37,315 --> 00:54:38,233
Or me.

844
00:54:39,359 --> 00:54:40,235
Or me.

845
00:54:41,236 --> 00:54:43,154
Or me.

846
00:54:43,822 --> 00:54:44,864
Or me.

847
00:55:01,339 --> 00:55:03,550
Guess you didn't need truth serum, huh?

848
00:55:05,135 --> 00:55:08,304
Sorry. This sucks,
but you're gonna have to hug me.

849
00:55:08,305 --> 00:55:10,640
Oh, Max.

850
00:55:14,352 --> 00:55:17,521
Just imagine
I'm hugging you really tight, okay?

851
00:55:17,522 --> 00:55:18,690
Okay.

852
00:55:27,407 --> 00:55:28,575
El.

853
00:55:29,200 --> 00:55:31,535
I know you're strong enough
to defeat Vecna.

854
00:55:31,536 --> 00:55:34,204
But he can retreat to the physical world,

855
00:55:34,205 --> 00:55:37,292
and we need to be ready
to fight him there too.

856
00:55:37,917 --> 00:55:41,921
We have bullets and fire,
but none of that helped those soldiers.

857
00:55:44,507 --> 00:55:45,508
I need to be there.

858
00:55:48,094 --> 00:55:49,303
And I'm ready.

859
00:55:49,304 --> 00:55:52,724
I'm ready to show him
I'm not afraid anymore.

860
00:56:09,032 --> 00:56:13,078
<i>That's a confirmation.
Anderson's on that patrol.</i>

861
00:56:14,079 --> 00:56:18,333
<i>Solid copy, Bravo One.
Maintain overwatch. Over.</i>

862
00:56:26,299 --> 00:56:27,591
Hey, McConnell.

863
00:56:27,592 --> 00:56:29,968
We got a delivery tonight
I don't know about?

864
00:56:29,969 --> 00:56:31,512
<i>That's a negative, private.</i>

865
00:56:31,513 --> 00:56:33,598
The hell are you doing, buddy?

866
00:56:36,726 --> 00:56:38,686
Showtime, Snookums!

867
00:56:39,270 --> 00:56:40,313
<i>Mellon</i>.

868
00:56:45,068 --> 00:56:46,236
Oh, shit!

869
00:56:48,238 --> 00:56:49,239
Pardon me!

870
00:56:50,657 --> 00:56:51,824
First gate cleared.

871
00:56:51,825 --> 00:56:55,120
Two hostiles, towers,
ten and eleven o'clock.

872
00:57:15,348 --> 00:57:17,142
Now comes the fun part.

873
00:57:47,046 --> 00:57:49,299
- Come on! Come on!
- Come on! Come on!

874
00:57:50,467 --> 00:57:51,843
Go! Go! Drive!

875
00:58:07,192 --> 00:58:08,735
Whoo-hey!

876
00:58:09,652 --> 00:58:10,487
Yeah!

877
00:58:12,947 --> 00:58:14,699
Jesus Christ.

878
00:58:15,283 --> 00:58:17,743
Everybody all right? Everybody okay?

879
00:58:17,744 --> 00:58:19,954
- Yeah.
- You all right? Everybody all right?

880
00:58:20,914 --> 00:58:22,874
Hey, nice shooting back there.

881
00:58:23,541 --> 00:58:24,375
You too.

882
00:58:26,711 --> 00:58:29,464
I kind of thought that
that was supposed to be the easy part.

883
00:58:30,340 --> 00:58:31,382
It was.

884
00:58:32,050 --> 00:58:33,009
You ready?

885
00:58:35,136 --> 00:58:36,012
Ready.

886
00:59:51,087 --> 00:59:52,088
It's time.

